1. Information We Collect

a. Personal Information
- Name and email (only when you sign in or reset password).
- College ID or roll number (optional, used for personalization).

b. Device & App Usage Information
- Device model and OS (for performance improvements).
- Crash logs or anonymous analytics (to debug and improve app features).
- Location data (only used locally for attendance/geofencing features ‚Äî not stored or shared).

c. User-Generated Content
- Timetable data, attendance status, and notes you input are saved locally or securely synced with your account, never shared without your consent.

2. How We Use Your Information

We use your data to:
- Provide personalized features (like smart alarms, schedules, and reminders).
- Allow syncing of data across devices.
- Improve app functionality and performance.
- Notify you about relevant updates (e.g., missed attendance, reminders).

3. Data Storage & Security

- Data is securely stored using Firebase and device storage.
- Attendance and timetable data are encrypted and accessible only by you.
- We do not sell, rent, or share your data with third-party advertisers.

4. Location Permissions

- Used only to mark attendance within your campus (via geofencing).
- We do not store or track your location beyond what is necessary for app functionality.

5. Third-Party Services

We use the following services:
- Firebase (authentication and data syncing)
- Expo Notifications (for sending alarms and alerts)
- Mapbox (for displaying the campus map)

Each third-party service follows its own privacy practices.

6. Your Rights

You have the right to:
- View or edit your stored data.
- Request deletion of your account data.
- Contact us for any privacy-related concerns.

